01/02/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Albanian Defence Minister Pandeli Majko departed on Sunday (1 February) for the United States, where he will hold meetings with top officials from the Pentagon and the State Department. 
Following his stay in the United States, Majko will proceed to Germany where he will attend the 40th Munich Conference on security policy.
On Saturday, Albanian Finance Minister Arben Malaj met with the head of the USAID mission in Tirana, Harry Burnholz. 
Malaj thanked USAID for the support it has given to the decentralisation process and the government's programme to privatise the water supply system. 
(ATA - 31/01/04)
